<task id="SPE-012" project="SDAP SPE Admin App">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement Business Unit List Endpoint</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1h</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, api, phase-1</tags>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <dependencies>SPE-009</dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Implement a read-only endpoint to list Dataverse business units at GET /api/spe/businessunits. The SPE Admin UI needs this to populate business unit dropdowns when creating or filtering container type configs. The endpoint queries the built-in businessunit Dataverse table and returns id, name, and parent BU id.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET API Developer</role>
  <goal>GET /api/spe/businessunits returns a list of business units from Dataverse with id, name, and parentBuId fields.</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Minimal API — use lambda or static method handler.</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/dataverse/web-api-client.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <context>
    <background>Business units are a built-in Dataverse concept used for organizational segmentation. The SPE Admin App uses BU assignment to scope container type configs to specific organizational units. The admin UI needs a list of available BUs for dropdown selection. This is a simple read-only endpoint that queries the standard businessunit table — no audit logging is needed since it is a non-mutating operation.</background>
  </context>
  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Define response model">Create a BusinessUnitDto with properties: id (Guid), name (string), parentBusinessUnitId (Guid?).</step>
    <step order="2" name="Implement GET endpoint">Add GET /api/spe/businessunits endpoint to the SpeAdmin route group that queries the Dataverse businessunit table.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Query Dataverse">Use the Dataverse Web API client to query businessunit table, selecting businessunitid, name, and _parentbusinessunitid_value columns.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Map and return">Map Dataverse response to BusinessUnitDto array and return 200.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Verify compilation">Run dotnet build to confirm the endpoint compiles correctly.</step>
  </steps>
  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/SpeAdmin/BusinessUnitEndpoints.cs</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/SpeAdmin/BusinessUnitDto.cs</output>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">GET /api/spe/businessunits returns a JSON array of business units.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Each business unit includes id, name, and parentBusinessUnitId fields.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The endpoint queries the Dataverse businessunit table.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">dotnet build succeeds.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
